CatDescriptText: Mrs. Nellie Wood, 2342 Webster Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you approve of women bartenders?" answer reads: "Sure, it gives women a chance. They are coming up and have to earn a living as much as anybody else."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Nellie Wood wearing hat, plaid shirt, and textured jacket, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, May Building with Thrift Drugs in background, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
